

HTTP 

Client -> Server 


HTTP Meesage

HTTP Request

Request Line 

Contains the HTTP method, URL (Uniform Resource Locator), and HTTP version.
Example: GET /index.html HTTP/1.1

Headers:

Additional information about the request.
Examples: Host, User-Agent, Accept.


Body(option)
Data sent to the server, often used in POST requests.




HTTP Response 

Status Line:

Contains the HTTP version, a three-digit status code, and a reason phrase.
Example: HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Headers:

Additional information about the response.
Examples: Content-Type, Content-Length, Server.

Body (Optional):
Data sent from the server to the client.
Example: HTML, JSON, or binary data.